com.xilinx.rapidwright.device

Class Wire

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.Wire

  • public class Wire
extends Object
    This class represents the device object called a wire in Vivado. It is uniquely identified in a device by the tile it belongs to and the specific wire within the tile, referred to by both a name and index that is unique to the tile type. Wire objects are dynamically created as when the device object is loaded, no wire objects are instantiated. Created on: Oct 8, 2015

      • getStartWire

        public Wire getStartWire()
        Will examine the node this wire belongs to and returns the wire that corresponds to the head or start of the node. Note, if the head is passed, this same object is returned.

        Vivado Tcl:

        lindex [get_wires -of [get_nodes -of $this]] 0

        Returns:
        The start wire of the node to which this wire belongs, or it returns this wire if it does not belong to a node.
        Since:
        2018.2.0
